      <!-- tab "panes" -->
      <div class="panes">
      	<div class="front-page-tab-body" id="Welcome-introduction">
            Welcome to the Smart City Energy platform
            <p class="intro">Understand your options... plan your future!</p>
            <div class="inner-content-welcome">
               <p> Within the project “Mitigation in Urban
				areas: Solutions for Innovative Cities”
				(MUSIC), five cities in North West Europe
				cooperate and exchange knowledge on
				how to implement an energy transition in
				their own city: Aberdeen, Ghent,
				Ludwigsburg, Montreuil and Rotterdam. 
				The integrated Geospatial Urban Energy Information and Support System framework (iGUESS)
				allows to integrate energy as a layer in urban planning. With this platform cities are able to 
				compute renewable energy and energy savings potential maps, urban heat island maps, 
				energy poverty maps and visualise CO2 emissions over time to identify opportunities 
				for energy exchange and monitor the effects of energy saving measures in their city.</p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="front-page-tab-body" id="view-some-data">
            View your data or register new datasets
            <p class="intro">iGUESS can show you any registered dataset on an interactive map of your city.</p>
            <div class="inner-content">
               <p><%= link_to "Explore maps of my city", :controller => 'maps'%></p>
               <p><%= link_to "See my datasets", :controller => 'datasets'%></p>
               <p><%= link_to "Register new data", :controller => 'datasets', :action => 'mass_import', :id => 1 %></p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="front-page-tab-body" id="run-a-module">
            Configure and run a calculation module
            <p class="intro">The module catalog shows the calculations that iGUESS can perform.</p>
            <div class="inner-content">
               <p><%= link_to "View module catalog", :controller => 'mod_configs', :anchor => 'module_catalog_tab'%></p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="front-page-tab-body" id="check-module">
            Check on the status of a running module
            <p class="intro">Logged in users can view the status of modules being run at their city.</p>
            <div class="inner-content">
               <p><%= link_to "See running modules", :controller => 'mod_configs'%></p>
            </div>            
         </div>
      </div>
</div>

